interviewProcess:
The interviews are designed to probe candidates' understanding of their school-based experiences. Interviews are held in a Trust school and candidates are given the opportunity to:
Talk about their understanding of the role of a primary classroom teacher;
Share and explore a text with a class or group of children;
Undertake a short written English exercise and a Maths task;
Take part in a short interview process.

Successful candidates will also be required to: 
Undertake a pre-course placement (10 days minimum) working as a volunteer in school with children in Key Stage 1 and/or Key Stage 2; 
Undertake an Enhanced Disclosure from the Disclosure Barring Service. 
Undertake a health check to demonstrate that s/he is physically and mentally fit to teach.
